Defendant Coryn P L Myer in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   
3 MONTHS JAIL; (consecutive to 14CM1648)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  Nicholas S. and Joseph B. unless contact approved by agent;
*Perform 30 Hours Community Service.
*Participate and complete Domestic Violence Counseling.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done. 

OTHER: The Court recommends that the Defendant obtain her GED.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (Apply cash bail and balance);

DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation.) 


Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.
